WEBVTT

00:06:58.069 --> 00:07:00.918
We've now been using
this process for eight years,

00:07:00.942 --> 00:07:03.958
and along the way, we've found
some incredible benefits

00:07:03.982 --> 00:07:06.116
to designing cities with children.

00:07:06.514 --> 00:07:09.921
First of all, kids think
differently from adults.

00:07:10.514 --> 00:07:12.283
And that's a good thing.

00:07:12.307 --> 00:07:14.426
Adults think about constraints,

00:07:14.450 --> 00:07:16.544
how much time will a project take,

00:07:16.568 --> 00:07:20.306
how much money will it cost
and how dangerous will it be.

00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:23.933
In other words,
"Are we going to get sued?"

00:07:23.957 --> 00:07:25.107
(Laughter)

00:07:25.553 --> 00:07:27.934
It's not that these
constraints aren't real,

00:07:27.958 --> 00:07:30.355
but if we kill off ideas
from the beginning,